    "custom_liquid_LDPqPq": {
      "type": "custom-liquid",
      "name": "Repairs",
      "settings": {
        "custom_liquid": "<style>\n.repair-categories {\n  max-width: 950px;\n  margin: 0 auto 80px auto;\n}\n\n.repair-category {\n  background: #f8f9fa;\n  border-radius: 12px;\n  padding: 35px;\n  margin-bottom: 30px;\n  border-left: 5px solid #111;\n}\n\n.repair-category h3 {\n  font-size: 26px;\n  margin-bottom: 14px;\n}\n\n.repair-category p,\n.repair-category li {\n  font-size: 16px;\n  line-height: 1.65;\n  color: #555;\n}\n\n.repair-link {\n  display: inline-block;\n  background:#111;\n  color:#fff !important;\n  padding: 12px 28px;\n  border-radius: 6px;\n  margin-top: 10px;\n  font-weight: 600;\n}\n\n@media (max-width: 900px) {\n  .repair-category { padding: 25px 20px; }\n}\n</style>\n\n<section id=\"repair-categories\" class=\"repair-categories\">\n\n<div class=\"repair-category\">\n<h3>iPad LCD Replacement</h3>\n<p>LCD faults affect display performance even when the glass appears intact. If your iPad shows lines, black spots, no display, or severe flickering, the LCD requires replacement.</p>\n<p><strong>Common LCD issues we fix:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>iPad turns on but shows no image</li>\n<li>Vertical or horizontal lines across the screen</li>\n<li>Severe colour distortion, dark patches, or flicker</li>\n<li>Ink-bleed or pressure marks under the glass</li>\n</ul>\n<p>We use genuine LCDs, ensuring brightness, colour accuracy, and pixel density remain as expected. in the models where the the screen is laminated (LCD and digitiser are fused togwether), we also make sure that the Apple Pencil works as it should after the repair.</p>\nView LCD Repair Pricing →\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"repair-category\">\n<h3>iPad Screen (Glass-Only) Repair</h3>\n<p>Glass-only repairs apply to models where the touchscreen digitiser is separate from the LCD panel. If the image is fine but the top glass is cracked, this is the correct repair.</p>\n<p><strong>Common symptoms:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Cracked or shattered front glass</li>\n<li>Touch input issues on specific areas</li>\n<li>Ghost touches or delayed response</li>\n<li>Glass lifting from the frame</li>\n</ul>\n<p>We carefully remove the damaged glass, replace it with a high-quality digitiser, and fully test touch accuracy and responsiveness - including Apple Pencil!.</p>\nView Glass Repair Pricing →\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"repair-category\">\n<h3>iPad Battery Replacement</h3>\n<p>iPad batteries degrade over time, especially on heavily used or older models. Worn batteries cause performance dips, unexpected shutdowns, or swelling.</p>\n<p><strong>Signs you need a new battery:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>iPad drains unusually fast</li>\n<li>Random shutdowns even above 20%</li>\n<li>Battery swelling pushing up the screen</li>\n<li>iPad only turns on when connected to a charger</li>\n<li>Overheating during normal use or charging</li>\n</ul>\n<p>We safely remove the original adhesive-bonded battery and install a fresh replacement, followed by a full charging and performance test.</p>\nView Battery Pricing →\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"repair-category\">\n<h3>iPad Charging Port Repair</h3>\n<p>If your iPad is no longer charging, charging intermittently, or fails to connect to accessories, the charging port may be damaged or obstructed.</p>\n<p><strong>Charging issues we solve:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Loose or unreliable charging connection</li>\n<li>iPad not charging at all</li>\n<li>Slow charging or “Not charging” message</li>\n<li>Corroded or bent port pins</li>\n</ul>\n<p>We repair or replace the charging port and test charging speed and cable stability after the repair.</p>\nView Charging Port Pricing →\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"repair-category\">\n<h3>iPad Diagnostic Service</h3>\n<p>If you're unsure what the issue is, our diagnostic service isolates the fault. We perform hardware checks, software analysis, and component testing to identify the exact cause of the problem.</p>\n<p><strong>Our diagnostic includes:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Touchscreen, LCD, and battery testing</li>\n<li>Charging system and power-line checks</li>\n<li>Logic board assessment and liquid damage inspection</li>\n<li>Connectivity testing (Wi-Fi, Bluetooth, cellular)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Once complete, we provide a full breakdown of findings and repair recommendations before proceeding.</p>\nBook Diagnostic Service →\n</div>\n\n</section>",
